race.comment: JAYASHREE (1) settled well back then made ground beaten 3L second up and could have had better luck. The former Sydney galloper has plenty up the sleeve and is suited by the step up to the mile. Fiore goes aboard and that's a decent push for her chances. MONTY ZOOMER (2) is also third-up and brings a narrow defeat from York over 1500m. That stacks up and he has an inside gate today and a handy 3kg claim. AMERICAN THIGHS (4) was tracking well before struggling last time in better grade. Will likely push forward and the 3kg claim in handy. Deserves consideration. I NEVER DREAMED (3) is third up and has been racing well without cracking a win. The blinkers come off, and she will come late again. In the mix.
